33973.name: Propstar
33973.description:
Generate property tables for all variants in your component sets by simply running Propstar, no configuration needed.


Creating tables

  1. Go to a page that has one or multiple component sets.
  2. Run Propstar.
  3. That's it! A table of instances will be generated to the right of the component set.


Reordering

To change the order of instances on the table, reorder the properties and values directly on the component set on Figma, using the controls on the right sidebar. Propstar will follow the same orders used on the component set.


The properties are evenly distributed across the rows and columns, prioritising rows.

34027.name: Table Builder
34027.description:
Table Builder

Table Builder lets you paste tabular data and generates tables from a single component.

For each entry in the spread sheet, Table Builder creates an instance of your original cell component, positions it in a grid and updates the cell's first child of type text with the data entry from the spreadsheet (Excel, Numbers, etc).


Usage

  1. Create a component that contains a text label (as a direct child)
  2. Select an instance of that component
  3. In the plugins menu, open Table Builder
  4. Copy tabular data from the spreadsheet and paste it into the text area of the plugin's UI
  5. Click on the Build Table button
